<HEADLINE>
OFFICE OF TRADE NEGOTIATIONS TO BE INAUGURATED
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  March 28 (CNA) 03/28/07  18:42:15 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
An Office of Trade Negotiations under the Ministry of Economic
Affairs (MOEA) will be established March 30, an MOEA spokesman
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The office will be in charge of negotiations on Taiwan's trade
and economic affairs, including talks on the Trade and Investment
Framework Agreement between Taiwan and the United States, free
trade agreements and the World Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
John C.C. Deng has been tapped as Taiwan's first chief
negotiator, a position that carries the same rights as an
ambassador, according to the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Deng will be moved from his present position as Taiwan's deputy
representative to the United States to head a staff of between 28
and 35 at the new office, the spokesman said.
</P>
